list.name: Changes
list.comment: For homework, I rewrote/cleaned/organized parts of my code - now, each row of Boxie objects is a distinct ArrayList (this gives me more flexibility regarding the functionality of the subclass objects of Boxie).

task.summary: This class, I read and learned about how to create fractal trees (how to use pushMatrix() and popMatrix()), and I implemented a fractal tree!
For homework, I made the fractal trees gradiant, randomized the branches (stochastic tree) and modified the code to create a circle design.

This class, I made my different designs objects (objects Cauliflower and Circlogo under the suberclass Boxies). In addition, I created an ArrayList to put (and later display) all of the Boxies. I have begun to insert the Cauliflower and Circlogo objects in the ArrayList.

For homework, I made the fractal tree gradiant, modified it to be a stochastic tree, and modified the code to work with circles. (This commit did not appear in GitHub, so I am adding two comments onto this commit).
This class, I made my different designs objects (objects Cauliflower and Circlogo under the suberclass Boxies). In addition, I created an ArrayList to put (and later display) all of the Boxies. I have begun to insert the Cauliflower and Circlogo objects in the ArrayList.

For homework, I modified the branch methods of Cauliflower and Circlogo to work for the ArrayList. I have begun to try to fix my code so that each Boxie object is separate (they are currently stacked on top of each other).

In class, I continued to work on fixing my code (so the Boxie objects do not appear stacked on top of each other). I also began experimenting with L-Systems as well as another Boxie object called Broccoli which may include a user interaction (perhaps mousePressed or keyPressed - TBD).
